# Backend Rules

Stack: Java 21, Spring Boot 3.5, MyBatis-Plus, Flyway, MySQL.

## Package Structure

```
com.credo.credo_server/
├── controller/   HTTP request/response only
├── service/      business rules
├── mapper/       MyBatis-Plus mapper interfaces
├── entity/       database entities
├── dto/          request/response objects
├── common/       unified response, error codes, exceptions
└── config/       framework configuration
```

- Controller: validate input, delegate to service, map to DTO. No business logic.
- Service: owns business rules and orchestration.
- Mapper: database access only via MyBatis-Plus.

## Persistence

Use MyBatis-Plus (not JPA). Mapper interfaces extend `BaseMapper<Entity>`.

Database schema changes: Flyway migrations only.
Migration naming: `V{number}__{snake_case_description}.sql`

## Unified Response

Wrap all API results in `ApiResponse<T>` with fields: `success`, `code`, `message`, `data`.
Business exceptions map to stable error codes; never leak stack traces.

## Testing

See `docs/testing-strategy.md`. Summary:

- Service: Mockito unit tests (primary)
- Controller: `@WebMvcTest` with mocked services
- Mapper/DB: Testcontainers + MySQL for integration tests
- Flyway migrations must pass in test environment before production
